evaluate

public void evaluate(ValueMap<?,?> bindings)
Description copied from interface: Expression
Evaluate this expression in its KB. Depending on the actual expression this can result in adding new statements or removing existing statements. However, this kind of modifications to the KB may not happen with every type of expression. For instance, expressions (such as a read query) that do not represent a function, or rule whose evaluation yields new statements which were not existing before.

Specified by:
evaluate in interface Expression<OWLList<Atom>>
Parameters:
bindings - A map of initial bindings possibly binding some of the variables used in this expression. Parameter can be null to evaluate this expression without the attempt to bind variables.

isTrue

public boolean isTrue(ValueMap<?,?> binding)
Description copied from interface: Condition
Check if this condition is entailed by its KB, whether it has at least one solution. If it consists of multiple atoms then it is checked if the conjunction of atoms is entailed by its KB.

Specified by:
isTrue in interface Condition<OWLList<Atom>>
Parameters:
binding - A map of initial bindings possibly binding some of the variables used in this condition. Parameter can be null to evaluate this expression without the attempt to bind variables.
Returns:
true if this condition is satisfied w.r.t. its own KB, after applying the given binding, that possibly grounds variables contained in this condition. This is equivalent to the call condition.isTrue(condition.getKB(), binding).

Check if this condition is entailed by the given model, whether it has at least one solution. If it consists of multiple atoms then it is checked if the conjunction of atoms is entailed by the given model.
